+# Shipshape Agents
+
+This project uses Shipshape for spec-driven development.
+
+## Stack
+- Language: JavaScript
+- Runtime: Node.js
+- Test runner: Cucumber.js
+- Package manager: npm
+
+## Directories
+- Implementation: `src/`
+- Specs: `features/`
+- Verification: `features/support/`
+- Assets: `data/`
+
+## Commands
+- `npm test`: Run Cucumber.js test suite
+- `npx cucumber-js`: Run Cucumber.js directly
+- `npx cucumber-js --dry-run`: Static discovery (undefined/unimplemented steps)
+
+## Project Configuration
+See `RIGGING.md` for machine-readable configuration.
+
+## Shipshape Workflow
+1. Captain writes durable specs in `.feature` files
+2. QM makes steps executable from current production code
+3. Crew implements minimal production changes
+4. Boatswain verifies, cleans, and commits
+5. Shipwright (harbour) inspects existing code and adds trace annotations
+
+## Current State
+- Fitted out for Shipshape
+- 2 passing scenarios
+- 1 production seam (`src/tide.js`)
+- 1 step definition file (`features/support/steps.js`)
+- Data files in `data/` directory
+
+## Next Steps
+- Add `@planks(...)` annotations to production seams
+- Write additional scenarios as needed
+- Maintain clean working tree between voyages
